# Enables a minimal desktop-capable build with common system integrations and
# hardware support.
*/* -startup-notification X networkmanager fontconfig udev dbus policykit udisks

# harfbuzz: Provides modern text shaping, which is required for correct
# rendering of code ligatures and complex text layouts.
#
# truetype: Enables the rendering of scalable fonts.
*/* harfbuzz truetype

# Disable the wxWidgets GUI toolkit to avoid compiling unnecessary graphical
# dependencies.
*/* -wxwidgets

# Printer and scanner
*/* cups scanner

# Disable legacy translation databases for modern IPP printers
net-print/cups-meta -foomatic
net-print/cups-filters -foomatic

# Ensures applications can use hardware-accelerated rendering
#
# opengl: This provides the standard desktop graphics API. Almost all 3D
# applications, terminal emulators with GPU acceleration, and desktop
# compositors require it.
#
# gles2: This is the OpenGL ES API. While originally designed for embedded
# systems, modern desktop software like web browsers (for WebGL support), media
# players, and GUI toolkits heavily rely on it for efficient rendering.
#
# egl: This acts as the interface between the rendering APIs (like OpenGL) and
# the underlying windowing system. It is required if you intend to run Wayland,
# and it heavily improves modern X11 setups.
#
# vulkan: This is the modern, low-overhead graphics and compute API. It provides
# direct access to the GPU, offering high performance and hardware acceleration
# for gaming, rendering engines, and modern window managers.
*/* opengl gles2 egl vulkan

# Spell
*/* spell aspell

# Flatpak
*/* flatpak

# Prune massive redundant typography packages from the install plan
# I do not need 14 different font families for a clean desktop layout. GNOME
# natively relies on media-fonts/cantarell for its system shell, and the
# terminal code layouts will look crisp using media-fonts/source-code-pro or
# dejavu.
media-fonts/fonts-meta -latin

# Compiles a headless, low-overhead version of the some tools
app-text/mupdf -X
sys-apps/lshw -gtk
net-firewall/firewalld -gui
media-gfx/img2pdf -gui
net-misc/unison -gtk
